Gunmen suspected to be bandits on Thursday night invaded the campus of Nuhu Bamalli Polytechnic in Zaria, Kaduna State, abducting an unspecified numbers of students and lecturers. SaharaReporters gathered that a student was also killed while others sustained injuries during the attack. SaharaReporters Media The attack is the latest in a series of the abduction of students and pupils by bandits operating in the state. The number of students abducted could not be ascertained as of the time of filing this report. Other information regarding the attack was still sketchy as of the time of filing this report. Recently, there have been similar attacks in schools in Kaduna with the abduction of students at the Federal College of Forestry and Mechanisation and Greenfield University.